"title": "6714: ransom",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6714",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The price paid for redemption, that is, for setting something or someone free from some form of obligation or captivity.</p>\n<h2>Ransom paid for what has been devoted to the Lord</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod13:12-Exod13:13\">EXO 13:12–13:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:11-Exod30:16\">EXO 30:11–30:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:20\">EXO 34:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev27:1-Lev27:33\">LEV 27:1–27:33</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num3:40-Num3:51\">NUM 3:40–3:51</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:14-Num18:17\">NUM 18:14–18:17</a></p>\n<h2>Ransom of a person's life instead of punishment</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:28-Exod21:32\">EXO 21:28–21:32</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Ransom from poverty and misfortune, including widowhood</h2>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:25-Lev25:28\">LEV 25:25–25:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:47-Lev25:55\">LEV 25:47–25:55</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth4:1-Ruth4:13\">RUT 4:1–4:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov13:8\">PRO 13:8</a></p>\n<h2>Limitations on ransom payments</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num35:31-Num35:32\">NUM 35:31–35:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev27:29\">LEV 27:29</a></p>\n<h2>Paying a ransom to God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps49:7-Ps49:8\">PSA 49:7–49:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:12-Exod30:16\">EXO 30:12–30:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job33:24\">JOB 33:24</a></p>\n<h2>Promises of redemption for the Lord's ransomed people</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa51:11\">ISA 51:11</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa35:10\">ISA 35:10</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:2\">ISA 40:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:3-Isa43:5\">ISA 43:3–43:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:11\">JER 31:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos13:14\">HOS 13:14</a></p>\n<h2>The death of Jesus Christ seen as a ransom</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:45\">MRK 10:45</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:28\">MAT 20:28</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:28\">ACT 20:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:5-1Tim2:6\">1TI 2:5–2:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:14\">TIT 2:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:15\">HEB 9:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:1\">2PE 2:1</a></p>\n<h2>The priceless value of the ransom of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:19-1Cor6:20\">1CO 6:19–6:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:23\">1CO 7:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:18-1Pet1:19\">1PE 1:18–1:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:9\">REV 5:9</a></p>",
